[normal]Written evidence submitted by the[bold] Africa Network Campaign on Education For All[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Quality Education For All Falls Short If [bold]Children With Disabilities Are Excluded[bold]Introduction[bold]Africa Network Campaign on Education For All (ANCEFA) is a voluntary, non-partisan and not-for profit network of national civil society organizations in Africa championing the cause for quality education
[normal] for all. The membership currently stand at 35 national education coalitions, each of them constituting diverse membership including NGOs, Teachers Unions, Human Rights, Child Rights and Education Rights Activists, Media Practitioners, Researchers, Academi
[normal]a, Community Based Organizations
[normal] and sub-thematic networks.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]ANCEFA envisions a 
[normal]Literate and Empowered Africa
[normal] where Quality Education For All is a reality enjoyed by all children, youth and adults, without any hindrances whatsoever. In order to realize its
[normal] dream, ANCEFA’s mandate is to enhance capacity of African Civil Society to efficiently and effectively push for universal access to quality education and development through campaign, advocacy, networking, research and resource mobilization.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]ANCEFA striv
[normal]es to support the emergence of vibrant civil society networks, coalitions and alliances that critically engage in EFA processes at the local, national, regional and international levels, among other core objectives and 
[normal]deploys such strategies as c
[normal]oalition 
